      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const transcript = $input.first().json.data;\n\nconst requestBody = {\n  model: \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\n  messages: [\n    {\n      role: \"system\",\n      content: \"You are an expert meeting analyst. Analyze meeting transcripts and extract structured information. Return ONLY valid JSON, no extra text.\"\n    },\n    {\n      role: \"user\",\n      content: `Extract structured information from this transcript.\n\nReturn ONLY a valid JSON object with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"meeting_title\": \"string\",\n  \"date\": \"string\",\n  \"participants\": [\"string\"],\n  \"key_decisions\": [\"string\"],\n  \"action_items\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"string - short actionable title, max 80 chars\",\n      \"description\": \"string - detailed context from the meeting\",\n      \"assignee\": \"string or null\",\n      \"priority\": \"High or Medium or Low\",\n      \"due_date\": \"YYYY-MM-DD or null\",\n      \"source_quote\": \"exact quote from transcript\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"discussion_highlights\": [\"string\"]\n}\n\nRules:\n- Extract ALL action items, even implicit ones like \"we should look into...\"\n- If no assignee is clear, set assignee to null\n- If no due date is mentioned, set due_date to null\n- For ambiguous items, set priority to Low\n- Include the exact source quote from the transcript\n- Do NOT invent items not discussed in the transcript\n\nHere is the transcript:\n\n${transcript}`\n    }\n  ],\n  temperature: 0.1,\n  response_format: { type: \"json_object\" }\n};\n\nreturn [{ json: requestBody }];\n"
      },
